Hi Abraham and Mostapha,

the problem does not depend on the case - even the simplest test does not work and even the most complex setup works on other computers. And yes, I have the latest version, updated it this morning, changed components on the canvas and still the same issue.
I've modified the code in isTheStudyOver like this to get more information printed: [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/4bIsJDjFjL4V3j8kEkpSFDSbo7QALL5U7MrhbVQewGki8Q8trzWmXqbJlarp7TrPCqYvltMbMzpNgUQmckEai*BG6muXZw-W/Capture.PNG) and after running a test I get these things printed out: [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/4bIsJDjFjL4OiI7qzdNyNDEZdNboAhT3X9DHrmUX0vFeu7VTlMYSzFZsXJ8y9YQiBPE-bJECuWn1N75GbNNmhgelIHmD6VuE/Capture2.PNG) (the cmd windows all open and running in the meantime).

As you can see the stdout does not get any line printed and the function returns after 0.3s without registering any activity...
